        insert Œ¥ T'
      else
        T'
    | none =>
      construction T hT i
```

The construction proceeds in stages. The `i`-th stage is defined recursively. The `0`-th stage is the set of all formulas `Œ¥` such that `œá ‚Üí Œ¥` is in `T`. The `i + 1`-th stage is defined using `match` on `decode i`. If `decode i` yields a formula `Œ¥`, we take the `i`-th construction set `T'` and either insert `Œ¥` into it (if a certain condition holds) or leave it as is. The condition is that for all finite sets of formulas `Œì` that are subsets of `T'`, if `Œì`'s conjunction implies `Œ¥` and leads to `Œæ` being true, then `Œ¥` should be in the set. The `none` case means the `i`-th set.

